race_name: VFW Sport Clips Help A Hero 200
race_comments: Denny Hamlin won the VFW SportClips Help a Hero 200, his 14th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory and fourth at Darlington Raceway. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 15 (unapproved adjustments) and No. 54 (missed driver introductions).

Joey Logano won the Drive to Stop Diabetes 300 at Bristol Motor Speedway, his 23rd victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series and second at the track. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Kyle Busch won the Food City 300 at Bristol Motor Speedway, his 73rd victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series and his eighth at BMS. Prior to the start of the race the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 90 (unapproved adjustments).

Denny Hamlin won the ToyotaCare 250 at Richmond International Raceway, his 12th victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series and third at the track. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: #44, 52, 70, 74 and 97 (unapproved adjustments).

Chase Elliott won the Virginia529 College Savings 250, his fourth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars 
dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 13, 28, 70 (unapproved adjustments).

race_name: Road America 180 Fired Up by Johnsonville
race_comments: Paul Menard won the Road America 180 Fired Up by Johnnsonville, his 3rd career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the field.

Kevin Harvick won the Drive4Clots.com 300 at Auto Club Speedway, his 46th victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated:  #70, 01 (unapproved adjustments).

Erik Jones won the Owens Corning AttiCat 300 at Chicagoland Speedway, his first win at the track and his second career win. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 1, No. 3, No. 52, No. 79 (unnaproved adjustments), No. 22 (back up car), No. 0 and No. 74 (missing drivers meeting).

Kyle Busch won the Furious 7 300, his 74th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: Nos. 1, 92 (unapproved adjustments).

Kyle Larson won the Ford EcoBoost 300, his third career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars 
dropped to the rear of the field: No. 97 (unapproved adjustments).

Kyle Busch won the Kansas Lottery 300, his 75th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars 
dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: Nos. 9 (backup car), 28 and 62 (unapproved adjustments).

Austin Dillon won the Boyd Gaming 300 at Las Vegas Motor Speedway, his third victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: #4, 13, 89 (unapproved adjustments), #52 (missed driver meeting).

Erik Jones won the O'Reilly 300 at Texas Motor Speedway, his first victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated:  #22, 52, 74 (unapproved adjustments).

Brad Keselowski won the O'Reilly Auto Parts Challenge, his 34th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the 
following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: Nos. 6 (back up car), 92 (missed driver introductions) and 89 
(missed driver meeting).

Brad Keselowski won the Kentucky 300, his 33rd career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, no cars dropped to the rear of the 
field.

Ryan Blaney won the VisitMyrtleBeach.com 300 at Kentucky Speedway, his fourth career victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series and his second at the track. Prior to the start of the race the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 54 (driver change and unapproved adjustments), No. 89 (unapproved adjustments).

Regan Smith won the Nationwide Children's Hospital 200 at Mid-Ohio Sports Car Course, his fifth victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series. Prior to the start of the race the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 0 (unapproved adjustments), No. 01 (driver change).

Joey Logano won the Winn Dixie 300 at Talladega Superspeedway, his 24th victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: #10 (driver change), #20, #54 (unapproved adjustments during impound), #17 (missing drivers meeting).

Joey Logano won the Axalta Faster. Tougher. Brighter. 200 at Phoenix International Raceway, his 22nd victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series and second 
at Phoenix. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated:  #13 and #40 (driver change); #56 
(unapproved adjustments).
Kyle Busch won the DAV 200 Honoring America's Veterans, his 76th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory.

race_name: Buckle Up 200 presented by Click It or Ticket
race_comments: Chris Buescher won the Buckle Up 200 presented by Click It or Ticket, his third career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 0 (unapproved adjustments); Nos. 13 and 40 (driver change).
Regan Smith won the Hisense 200, his sixth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory.

Ryan Reed won the Alert Today Florida 300 at Daytona International Speedway, his first victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field: #44 (Unapproved Adjustments), #10 (Driver Change), #18, 8, 01 (Backup Car).

Austin Dillon won the Subway Firecracker 250, his fifth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: No. 74 (missing driver intros), No. 52 (unapproved adjustments).

Kevin Harvick won the Hisense 250 at Atlanta Motor Speedway, his 45th victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series and fourth at Atlanta. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: #14 (unapproved adjustments).

field.

Denny Hamlin won the Lakes Region 200, his 13th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory, and first at New Hampshire Motor Speedway. Prior to the start of the race, the following car dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: No. 24 (unapproved adjustment).

Joey Logano won the Zippo 200 at The Glen, his 25th career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: Nos. 25 and 88 (unapproved adjustment), No. 40 (back up car and driver change).

Austin Dillon won the Hisense 300, his fourth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of  the field for the reason indicated: No. 55, 84 (unapproved adjustments).

race_name: Drive for the Cure 300 Pres by Blue Cross and Blue Shield of NC
race_comments: Austin Dillon won the Drive for the Cure 300 presented by Blue Cross Blue Shield of North Carolina, his sixth career NASCAR XFINITY Series victory. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reason indicated: Nos. 13, 14 (unapproved adjustments).

Chris Buescher won the 3M 250 at Iowa Speedway, his second victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series. Prior to the start of the race, the following cars dropped to the rear of the field for the reasons indicated: Nos. 13, 29, 40, 42, 70 (unapproved adjustments); No. 20 (driver change).

race_name: US Cellular 250 presented by New Holland
race_comments: Ryan Blaney won the U.S. Cellular 250 presented by New Holland, his third victory in the NASCAR XFINITY Series and first at Iowa Speedway. Prior to the start of the race the No. 54 dropped to the rear of the field for a driver change.
